Is a pushing SCM and Agentless,
this means the instances won't
need anything pre-installed, thus,
Ansible will reach the instances
trough SSH connection. When the
master has new changes, Ansible
will push the new state to the
instances via SSH

div.div:
Agentless could be better for
continous and quick deployments,
but is not as safe as an Agent based
tool, because the agents and the
master will ensure an encrypted
communication, but it is harder to
manage. Also, the pulling strategy
ensures a safer state of the server
because it is posible to recover a
previous state.

popular configuration management
tools, it has a wide community and
an easier learning path than others.
Is one of the most used tools in the
industry and you don't need to learn
a new language as Ruby for using
tools as Puppet or Chef.
